docs.lead_paragraph: The steamship New-York, of the Bremen line, from Southampton, July 12, arrived here last evening. Her advices are not so late as those of the North Briton, and embrace nothing relative to the Treaty of Peace. We extract liberally from our files in illustration of events preceding that result.

docs.lead_paragraph: General JOSE.A. PAEZ and his companions, who came from Veneuzela in the brig Rowena, arriving at Philadelphia on Sunday, proceeded directly to this City, and put up at the Union-place Hotel. The reason of the disgust of General PA?? at the state of things in Veneuzela grew out of the jealousy of General CASTRO.

docs.snippet: A Treaty of Peace has been signed between the Emperors of France and Austria, and the Italian war has been brought to a sudden conclusion. We Received this highly important intelligence by North Briton, which arrived at Quebec yesterday, with advices...
docs.lead_paragraph: A Treaty of Peace has been signed between the Emperors of France and Austria, and the Italian war has been brought to a sudden conclusion. We Received this highly important intelligence by North Briton, which arrived at Quebec yesterday, with advices four days later-she having left Liverpool on the 13th.

docs.lead_paragraph: MORTALITY.-From the 16th to the 23d inst, there were 149 deaths in Brooklyn, according to the official statement of Dr. BoYD, Health Officer. These are classified as follows: men, 9; women, 18; boys, 63; girls, 59; adults, 27; children, 122; males, 72; females, 77; colored persons, I.

docs.lead_paragraph: HARRIET MARTINEAU ON THEO?? FOURTH.--In HARRIET MARTINNAU'S last letter to the Anti-Slavery Standard, dated at Ambleside, July 4, she says: "The Fourth of July comes to those who know its significance under widely different aspects to-day. I imagine you, Sir, sitting in the midst of the din of rejoicing in your great City. .

headline.main: RUFUS CHOATE.; FUNERAL OF MR. CHOATE. MEETING OF THE NEW-YORK BAR. Addresses by Mr. Hiram Kotchum and Ex-Judge Peabody. MEETING OF THE CITIZENS OF BOSTON. Tributes to the Memory of the Hon. Rufus Choate. ADDRESS OF EDWARD EVERETT.

docs.snippet: The steamship New-York, from Southampton on the 12th inst., and the North Briton, from Liverpool on the 13th, will bring the next European advices. The former will arrive at this port, and the latter at Quebec.

headline.main: THE LOSS OF THE ALMA.; A Story of Shipwreck and Suffering.

docs.lead_paragraph: On the morning of the 15th intelligence reached Aden of the stranding of the Alma on the Moosedjerah, one of the reefs, or rather islets, which form the Kharnesh group, about 70 miles to the north of Perim. in the Red Sea.
